Homepage: https://github.com/yicechuhai/rk3588-industrial-rt-middleware
Description: RK3588 Industrial Protocol Real-Time Middleware
 Real-time middleware for industrial control applications
 on Rockchip RK3588 SoC and compatible ARM64 platforms.
 .
 Features:
  - CPU core isolation with AMP support (big.LITTLE A55 + A76)
  - IRQ affinity configuration for deterministic latency
  - PREEMPT_RT kernel build automation (apply_rt_patch.sh)
  - One-click real-time system setup (setup_realtime.sh)
  - Cyclictest-style jitter monitor with histogram analysis
  - Latency analysis and report generation (Markdown/JSON)
  - Modbus TCP server (port 502, built-in + pymodbus support)
  - OPC UA server (port 4840, with node tree management)
  - YAML register map configuration and conversion
  - IgH EtherCAT Master auto-installer
  - Debian packaging with multi-architecture support
 .
 Performance Targets:
  - PREEMPT_RT: P99 < 50us, Max < 80us (Grade A+)
  - PREEMPT_VOLUNTARY: P99 < 500us, Max < 5ms (Grade B)
  - Xenomai/Cobalt: P99 < 25us, Max < 30us
 .
 Target Platforms:
  - RK3588-based industrial controllers (Rock 5, Orange Pi 5, etc.)
  - Compatible ARM64 SBCs with PREEMPT_RT kernel
  - x86_64 development environments (amd64 package)
